# Redeploy after code or feature changes

Whenever **features are added** or **code changes are made** that affect the running application, **redeploy** so those changes are reflected in the live app.

## What to do

1. After completing the code/feature work, run the full deploy from **repo root**:
   - `.\scripts\nanoclaw-deploy.ps1 -AppName library`
   - (Use the app name for this project, e.g. `library`; or `$env:NANOCLAW_APP_NAME` if set.)
2. Do **not** ask for permission; run the deploy as part of the same response/task.
3. When the script finishes, confirm in your reply that the app was deployed and give the **Frontend URL** (e.g. https://library.vercel.app) so the user can verify the changes.

## When this applies

- New or changed frontend pages, components, or API routes.
- New or changed backend routes or behavior.
- DB migrations or schema changes (deploy runs migrations).
- Any change that should be visible or usable in the live application.

If the user explicitly says "do not deploy" or "local only", skip the deploy step.
